From: Kamil Lulko <limakzagan@gmail.com>
Subject: ntdll/unix: spoof AMD64 as native machine in SystemSupportedProcessorArchitectures (11.9 port)

Port of the old patch 0010 (TONEX-verified on wine 10.10) onto 11.9's
rewritten handler; it was dropped in the 11.9 rebase, which regressed
Inno Setup installers back to "This program can only be installed on
versions of Windows designed for the following processor architectures:
x64" (hit by the BIAS FX 2 installer on a fresh prefix, 2026-06-10).

Upstream 11.9 faithfully emulates Windows-on-ARM: IsWow64Process2 /
SystemSupportedProcessorArchitectures report native_machine=ARM64 and
hide AMD64 from the non-2 class. Inno Setup >= 6.3 resolves the machine
via IsWow64Process2 and rejects native=ARM64 when the installer says
ArchitecturesAllowed=x64 - even though FEX-Emu translates x86_64 PE
transparently. Swap AMD64 into the native slot of the user-facing reply
and demote the real ARM64 to a non-native entry (still listed). Wine's
internal loader keeps using the server-side native_machine=ARM64, so
aarch64-windows system DLLs still load. Pairs with patch 0013
(SystemCpuInformation spoof for 32-bit wow64 callers) and the
seedWindowsVersion Version-strip on the Kotlin side.

--- a/dlls/ntdll/unix/system.c
+++ b/dlls/ntdll/unix/system.c
@@ -4134,14 +4134,36 @@
 
         for (i = 0; i < supported_machines_count; i++)
         {
-#ifdef __aarch64__
-            if (class == SystemSupportedProcessorArchitectures &&
-                supported_machines[i] == IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_AMD64)
-                continue;
-#endif
             machines_to_return[machines_to_return_count] = supported_machines[i];
             machines_to_return_count++;
         }
+#ifdef __aarch64__
+        /* vstpoc (11.9 port of old patch 0010): present AMD64 as the NATIVE
+         * machine in the user-facing reply. Upstream faithfully emulates
+         * Windows-on-ARM here (native=ARM64, AMD64 hidden from the non-2
+         * class), but pre-WoA installers (Inno Setup >= 6.3 reads
+         * IsWow64Process2's native_machine: IK TONEX 1.12, BIAS FX 2) reject
+         * native=ARM64 with "this program can only be installed on ... x64"
+         * even though FEX-Emu translates their x86_64 code transparently.
+         * Swap AMD64 into the native slot and demote the REAL ARM64 to a
+         * non-native entry (still listed, like the verified 10.10 behavior).
+         * Wine's internal loader keeps using the server-side
+         * native_machine=ARM64, so aarch64-windows system DLLs still load —
+         * only this user-facing reply lies. Pairs with patch 0013
+         * (SystemCpuInformation spoof for 32-bit wow64 callers). */
+        if (machines_to_return_count && machines_to_return[0] == IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_ARM64)
+        {
+            for (i = 1; i < machines_to_return_count; i++)
+            {
+                if (machines_to_return[i] == IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_AMD64)
+                {
+                    machines_to_return[i] = IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_ARM64;
+                    machines_to_return[0] = IMAGE_FILE_MACHINE_AMD64;
+                    break;
+                }
+            }
+        }
+#endif
 
         len = (machines_to_return_count + 1) * sizeof(*machines);
         if (size < len)
